Compliance with Ethical Requirements.question:
Based on our assessment of independence requirements, we confirm that we have not identified any threats relevant to ethical requirements and if any threat has been identified the following steps have been applied:

- Eliminating the circumstances that are creating the threats;
- Applying safeguards to reduce the threats to an acceptable level;
- Declining or ending the specific professional activity.

Have any prohibited services u/s 144 of the Companies Act, 2013 as listed below been provided to the entity (directly/indirectly to the company or its holding or subsidiary company)?
- Accounting and book keeping services;
- Internal audit;
- Design and implementation of any financial information system;
- Actuarial services;
- Investment advisory services;
- Investment banking services;
- Rendering of outsourced financial services;
- Management services; and
- Any other kind of services prescribed.

Assess Engagement Risk.question:
Assess engagement risk based on the following external factors:
- Management characteristics and integrity, the management environment and organizational and management structure;
- Management’s commitment to the appropriate application of reliable financial reporting framework;
- Management’s commitment to implementing and maintaining internal control;
- Financial results and financial viability;
- Nature of business;
- Business and regulatory environment;
- Business relationships and related parties;
- Other risk factors associated with the prospective or existing Engagement.

In assessing internal factors, the considerations ordinarily include the following:
- Availability and competency of Partners and Professional Staff;
- Compliance with ethical and Independence requirements;
- Professional Services;
- Engagement economics.

Agreeing the Terms of Audit Engagement.question:
Record the agreed terms of the audit engagement in an audit engagement letter or other suitable form of written agreement which includes:
- The objective and scope of audit of financial statements;
- The responsibilities of the auditor;
- The responsibilities of the management;
- A statement that because of the inherent limitations of an audit together with the inherent limitations of the internal control, an unavoidable risk exists that some material misstatements may not be detected even though audit is properly planned and performed in accordance with relevant auditing standards;
- The applicable financial reporting framework for preparation of the financial statements; and
- Reference to the expected form and content of any reports to be issued by the auditor including a statement that there may be circumstances in which a report may differ from its expected form and content.
